\par {\fs28 wSendmail 1.3 for Win95/NT}
\par \pard \nowidctlpar 
\par wSendmail  is a handy utility for sending emails from programs, the command-line or directly from HTML Forms on Windows based systems (Win95 and NT). I wrote the program in order to implement a mail-response feature on a WEB service. It appears that most 
pearl scripts and .c CGI programs are written for UNIX systems and depend 
on the UNIX sendmail program to work. I don't have the man file for UNIX sendmail, so wSendmail is not comforming to the UNIX line syntax. The program is first of all a CGI-BIN utility for mail-response. 
\par 
\par In CGI mode, it must run as a standard CGI-BIN app, and {\b not} as WIN-CGI! (If I have got it right, WIN-CGI is a interface to get around limitations in Visual Basic. wSendmail is written in c++).
\par 
